---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---

<Base title="Privacy — Wayfinders" description="How Wayfinders handles your personal information.">
  <div class="container">
    <h1>Privacy notice</h1>
    <p class="updated">Last updated: May 2026.</p>

    <p>Wayfinders is a small, free, Christian career discernment cohort. This notice explains how we handle the personal information you share when you apply or take part.</p>

    <h2>Who we are</h2>
    <p>Wayfinders is run by Ben Hollebon, an individual based in the UK. Wayfinders is not a registered charity or company at the moment. Contact: <a href="mailto:hello@wayfinders.org.uk">hello@wayfinders.org.uk</a>.</p>

    <h2>What we collect</h2>
    <p>When you apply to a cohort, we collect:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Your name</li>
      <li>Your email address</li>
      <li>Your location (town/city, not full address)</li>
      <li>Your age range</li>
      <li>Your job description</li>
      <li>Your church or faith tradition</li>
      <li>The decision you're sitting with and your reflections on it</li>
      <li>Your answers to honest-check questions (ordained ministry, crisis status, ability to commit)</li>
    </ul>

    <p>When you take part in a cohort, we additionally hold:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Your phone number (for WhatsApp groups)</li>
      <li>Notes on your mentor match</li>
      <li>Light updates from your mentor on whether the match is working</li>
    </ul>

    <p>We do not collect salary, sensitive demographic data (unless you choose to share it), health data beyond the crisis-check question, or special category data under UK GDPR.</p>

    <h2>How we use it</h2>
    <p>The information you give us is used to:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Decide whether the cohort is the right fit for you</li>
      <li>Match you with an appropriate mentor</li>
      <li>Run the sessions (logistics, scheduling)</li>
      <li>Stay in touch about the cohort and, if you want, future cohorts</li>
      <li>Improve future cohorts (anonymously)</li>
    </ul>
    <p>We do not use it for marketing, advertising, or analytics. We don't profile you. We don't sell or share data with third parties for commercial reasons.</p>

    <h2>Where it's stored</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Application data: Google Forms / Google Sheets, accessible only by Ben</li>
      <li>Mentor matching: a single Google Sheet, accessible only by Ben</li>
      <li>Email: Google Workspace inbox at hello@wayfinders.org.uk</li>
      <li>WhatsApp messages: stored on participants' phones; Wayfinders doesn't control or back this up</li>
    </ul>
    <p>All data is held in the UK or under UK-equivalent protections via Google's standard contractual clauses.</p>

    <h2>Lawful basis</h2>
    <p>We process your information on the basis of your consent (you chose to apply) and our legitimate interest in running a small mentoring cohort. You can withdraw consent at any time.</p>

    <h2>How long we keep it</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Successful applications:</strong> as long as you remain in the cohort and alumni network. If you leave, we delete your data within 90 days of you asking.</li>
      <li><strong>Unsuccessful applications:</strong> 12 months, in case you'd like to apply for a future cohort, then deleted.</li>
      <li><strong>Mentor session notes:</strong> deleted within 30 days of cohort end.</li>
      <li><strong>Anonymised learning notes:</strong> kept indefinitely (no identifying information).</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Your rights</h2>
    <p>Under UK GDPR you have the right to:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>See what data we hold about you</li>
      <li>Correct anything that's wrong</li>
      <li>Have it deleted ("the right to be forgotten")</li>
      <li>Withdraw consent</li>
      <li>Complain to the Information Commissioner's Office (ICO)</li>
    </ul>
    <p>To exercise any of these, email <a href="mailto:hello@wayfinders.org.uk">hello@wayfinders.org.uk</a>.</p>

    <h2>Confidentiality of cohort content</h2>
    <p>The substance of what is shared in sessions, in WhatsApp groups, and in 1:1s is bound by Wayfinders' <a href="/principles">confidentiality principles</a>. These go beyond GDPR and apply to all participants &mdash; mentees, mentors, and Ben.</p>

    <h2>Safeguarding</h2>
    <p>If you disclose information that suggests you or someone else is at risk of harm, we may need to contact a professional safeguarding adviser or, in cases of imminent risk, emergency services. We will tell you when we're doing this wherever it's safe to do so.</p>

    <h2>Changes to this notice</h2>
    <p>We'll update this notice when we change how we handle data. The current version always lives here with the date at the top.</p>

    <h2>Questions</h2>
    <p><a href="mailto:hello@wayfinders.org.uk">hello@wayfinders.org.uk</a></p>
  </div>
</Base>

